#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/family.phtml:450
msgid ""
"For each marriage decade, the share of those marriages that are recorded as "
"ending in divorce. Tracks how openly the tree records dissolutions over time "
"rather than the underlying historical rate."
msgstr ""
"For each marriage decade, the share of those marriages that are recorded as "
"ending in divorce. Tracks how openly the tree records dissolutions over time "
"rather than the underlying historical rate."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/family.phtml:539
msgid ""
"For every couple where both spouses carry a recorded date of death, the gap "
"in whole years between the two death dates lands the couple in a 5-year "
"band. The 50+ band captures the long tail. Couples where neither spouse has "
"a recorded death date are excluded — the interval is undefined without both "
"anchors."
msgstr ""
"Dla każdej pary, w której oboje małżonkowie mają zarejestrowaną datę zgonu, "
"różnica w pełnych latach między obiema datami umieszcza parę w pięcioletnim "
"paśmie. Pasmo 50+ obejmuje długi ogon. Pary bez zarejestrowanej daty zgonu "
"obu małżonków są wykluczone, ponieważ bez obu kotwic odstępu nie da się "
"określić."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/tree-health.phtml:122
msgid ""
"For every couple where both spouses have at least one parent recorded, the "
"widget walks each spouse's ancestor tree up to four generations and "
"intersects the two sets. A non-empty intersection means the couple share at "
"least one common ancestor. That is the classic signature of cousin marriage "
"and pedigree collapse."
msgstr ""
"Dla każdej pary, w której każde z małżonków ma zapisanego co najmniej "
"jednego rodzica, moduł przemierza drzewo przodków obojga małżonków do "
"czterech pokoleń i krzyżuje oba zbiory. Niepuste przecięcie oznacza, że para "
"dzieli co najmniej jednego wspólnego przodka. To klasyczna sygnatura "
"małżeństwa kuzynostwa i implekszji rodowodu."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/family.phtml:393
msgid ""
"For every fully-dated child in the tree (BIRT carrying both a day and a "
"month) the widget checks whether at least one sibling in the same FAM shares "
"the BIRT julian-day. Same-day siblings are counted as a multiple-birth set; "
"INDI:ASSO links between two children of the same FAM whose BIRT dates sit "
"within one day of each other also merge into a set, so cross-midnight twins "
"still count when the tree author recorded the association explicitly. The "
"chart draws one series per multiplicity that actually occurs in the tree "
"(twins, triplets, quadruplets, quintuplets and above) — each series shows "
"that multiplicity's per-century share of all dated births. Year-only BIRT "
"records (day and month both blank) are intentionally excluded — they would "
"turn every \"0 0 1829\" sibling group into a phantom multi-birth set. "
"Centuries below 200 fully-dated children are dropped to keep the curve from "
"spiking on small denominators."
msgstr ""
"Dla każdego w pełni datowanego dziecka (BIRT z dniem ORAZ miesiącem) widget "
"sprawdza, czy co najmniej jedno rodzeństwo w tej samej FAM dzieli juliański "
"dzień BIRT. Rodzeństwo z tego samego dnia liczy się jako poród mnogi; "
"powiązania INDI:ASSO między dwojgiem dzieci tej samej FAM, których daty BIRT "
"są od siebie oddalone o co najwyżej jeden dzień, również są łączone. Wykres "
"rysuje jedną serię na multipliczność (bliźnięta, trojaczki, czworaczki, "
"pięcioraczki i więcej). Zapisy tylko z rokiem są pomijane."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/tree-health.phtml:304
msgid ""
"For every individual in the tree the widget counts how many descendants are "
"recorded below them across all generations. A descendant reached through two "
"different grandparents is counted once per ancestor. The ranking surfaces "
"the people whose branches actually carry the rest of the recorded lineage."
msgstr ""
"Dla każdej osoby w drzewie moduł liczy, ilu potomków jest zarejestrowanych "
"poniżej w sumie wszystkich pokoleń. Potomek osiągnięty przez dwóch różnych "
"dziadków jest liczony raz na przodka. Ranking pokazuje osoby, których "
"gałęzie faktycznie niosą resztę zarejestrowanej linii."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/places.phtml:57
msgid ""
"For every individual the widget collects every distinct PLAC value that "
"appears on any of their level-1 events (BIRT, DEAT, BAPM, BURI, RESI, …) and "
"counts the unique places. Duplicates within the same individual (e.g. BIRT "
"and DEAT both in Hamburg) collapse to one place, so the count reflects "
"geographic mobility rather than how many events are recorded. The average is "
"across every individual with at least one PLAC sample; individuals with no "
"place data at all are excluded."
msgstr ""
"For every individual the widget collects every distinct PLAC value that "
"appears on any of their level-1 events (BIRT, DEAT, BAPM, BURI, RESI, …) and "
"counts the unique places. Duplicates within the same individual (e.g. BIRT "
"and DEAT both in Hamburg) collapse to one place, so the count reflects "
"geographic mobility rather than how many events are recorded. The average is "
"across every individual with at least one PLAC sample; individuals with no "
"place data at all are excluded. The distribution on the right shows how "
"those counts split across 1 / 2 / 3 / 4 / 5+ distinct places per person — a "
"high tail signals migrant ancestors, a heavy bar at \\"

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/life-span.phtml:344
msgid ""
"For every individual with both a birth and a death date recorded, the "
"lifespan in whole years is derived. Each birth century forms one cohort and "
"is sampled at ages 0, 10, 20, up to 100 — the value at age N is the share of "
"the cohort that lived at least N years. Cohorts below 30 recorded "
"individuals are dropped because a single death would shift the curve by more "
"than three percentage points."
msgstr ""
"Dla każdej osoby z zarejestrowaną datą urodzenia i zgonu obliczana jest "
"długość życia w pełnych latach. Każde stulecie urodzenia tworzy jedną "
"kohortę próbkowaną w wieku 0, 10, 20 aż do 100. Wartość w wieku N to udział "
"kohorty, który żył co najmniej N lat. Kohorty poniżej 30 zarejestrowanych "
"osób są pomijane, ponieważ pojedynczy zgon przesunąłby krzywą o ponad trzy "
"punkty procentowe."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/life-span.phtml:147
msgid ""
"For every individual with both a birth and a death date the widget computes "
"the number of days lived. A death within five years (1826 days) of birth "
"counts as under-5 mortality. The line groups those children by their birth "
"century so the historical decline becomes visible (typical 1700s value 30 to "
"40 percent, modern below 2 percent). Individuals with only a birth or only a "
"death date are silently excluded, since the rate cannot be determined "
"without both anchors. Per-century cohorts below 5 children are suppressed "
"because a single dead child would spike the line by more than 10 percentage "
"points."
msgstr ""
"Dla każdej osoby z odnotowaną datą urodzenia i śmierci obliczany jest okres "
"życia. Śmierć w ciągu pięciu lat (1826 dni) od urodzenia liczy się jako "
"umieralność dzieci poniżej 5 lat. Linia grupuje te dzieci według stulecia "
"urodzenia. Spadek historyczny staje się dzięki temu widoczny (w XVIII wieku "
"zwykle 30 do 40 procent, dziś poniżej 2 procent). Osoby z tylko jedną z "
"dwóch dat są pomijane. Bez obu kotwic nie można określić wskaźnika. Stulecia "
"z mniej niż 5 zapisanymi dziećmi są ukrywane. Pojedynczy zgon poruszyłby "
"linię w przeciwnym razie o ponad 10 punktów procentowych."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/tree-health.phtml:118
msgid ""
"For every individual, this bucket counts how many generations of descendants "
"are recorded below them in the tree. Bucket 0 = leaf (no descendants), "
"bucket N = an individual whose deepest verified descendant is N generations "
"younger."
msgstr ""
"For every individual, this bucket counts how many generations of descendants "
"are recorded below them in the tree. Bucket 0 = leaf (no descendants), "
"bucket N = an individual whose deepest verified descendant is N generations "
"younger."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/family.phtml:357
#, php-format
msgid ""
"For every marriage decade the bar is split into segments by the number of "
"children (0, 1, 2 … 10+). Each bar is normalised to 100 %%, so decades with "
"very different family counts can be compared side by side."
msgstr ""
"Dla każdej dekady ślubu słupek jest podzielony na segmenty według liczby "
"dzieci (0, 1, 2 … 10+). Każdy słupek jest znormalizowany do 100 %%, aby "
"dekady o bardzo różnej liczbie rodzin można było porównywać obok siebie."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/names.phtml:122
msgid ""
"For every parent-child pair of the same sex (father / son and mother / "
"daughter) where both individuals carry a recorded given name, the widget "
"tokenises each name and counts the pair as a match when at least one token "
"appears on both sides. Order and position do not matter. The chart carries "
"one series per sex pairing on a shared X axis, so the two traditions can be "
"compared at a glance. Centuries with fewer than 10 recorded pairs are "
"suppressed independently per series because a single match would swing the "
"rate by more than 10 percentage points."
msgstr ""
"Dla każdej pary rodzic-dziecko tej samej płci (ojciec / syn i matka / "
"córka), w której obie osoby mają zarejestrowane imię, moduł dzieli każde "
"imię na tokeny i liczy parę jako dopasowanie, gdy co najmniej jeden token "
"występuje po obu stronach. Kolejność ani pozycja nie mają znaczenia. Wykres "
"niesie jedną serię na zestawienie płci na wspólnej osi X, aby obie tradycje "
"można było porównać na pierwszy rzut oka. Stulecia z mniej niż 10 "
"zarejestrowanymi parami są tłumione niezależnie dla każdej serii, ponieważ "
"pojedyncze dopasowanie zmieniłoby wskaźnik o ponad 10 punktów procentowych."

